To the Estate Services Department at {{ institution_name }}:

I am writing to formally notify you of the passing of {{ deceased_name }}, date of birth {{ deceased_dob }}, who passed away on {{ date_of_death }}.

I have been appointed as the executor / personal representative of the Estate of {{ deceased_name }} and am authorized to act on behalf of the estate.

I respectfully request that you:

  1. Place a hold on all accounts associated with the deceased
  2. Provide the account balance(s) as of the date of death ({{ date_of_death }})
  3. Send any required claim, transfer, or closure forms to the address listed above
  4. Cease any automatic payments, withdrawals, or recurring charges

Enclosed with this letter, please find:
  - Certified copy of the death certificate
  - Letters Testamentary (or Letters of Administration), if required

Please contact me at your earliest convenience to confirm receipt of this notice and to advise on the next steps required to close or transfer the above-referenced account(s).

I appreciate your patience and assistance during this difficult time.

